**Task complete.** Here's what was implemented:

### Floating Learning Toolbar with Text Actions

**Files created/modified:**
- `apps/extension/src/content/floatingToolbar.ts` (new, 407 lines) — Full toolbar content script
- `apps/extension/src/content/index.ts` (modified) — imports the new toolbar module

**Toolbar behavior:**
- Appears on any webpage when user selects text (mouse or Shift+Arrow selection)
- Positions intelligently above the selection (flips below if insufficient space)
- Hides on: click outside, Escape key, scroll, or clicking the × button
- Fades in/out with smooth animation
- Has an arrow pointing to the selection

**7 action buttons** grouped with a visual divider:
| Save actions (direct) | AI actions (saves + checks config) |
|---|---|
| 📖 Save Word (vocabulary) | 💡 Explain Meaning |
| 📝 Save Sentence (sentence) | ✂️ Simplify Text |
| ⚠️ Mistake Note (mistake) | 🌐 Translate to VN |
| | 🎯 IELTS Vocab |

- **Save actions** write to `chrome.storage.local` and update daily progress
- **AI actions** save the text, then check if AI is configured — shows a contextual toast either way
- All actions use the existing `UPDATE_PROGRESS` messaging pattern

**Settings integration:**
- Respects `extensionSettings.floatingToolbar` (reads on init via `chrome.storage.sync`, live-updates via `storage.onChanged`)
- Defaults to enabled if setting is absent

**Build & typecheck:** Both pass cleanly.
